<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>UGENE Command Line Interface on UGENE Documentation</title><link>https://ugene.net/docs/ugene-command-line-interface/</link><description>Recent content in UGENE Command Line Interface on UGENE Documentation</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://ugene.net/docs/ugene-command-line-interface/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>CLI Options</title><link>https://ugene.net/docs/ugene-command-line-interface/cli-options/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ugene.net/docs/ugene-command-line-interface/cli-options/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="cli-options">CLI Options&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>&lt;em>--help | -h [&amp;lt;option_name&amp;gt; | &amp;lt;task_name&amp;gt;]&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Shows help information. For example:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene --help &lt;span style="color:#75715e">## Shows general UGENE CLI help.&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene -h
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene --help&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>&amp;lt;option_name&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e">## Shows help for the &amp;lt;option_name&amp;gt; option.&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene -h &amp;lt;option_name&amp;gt;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene --help&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>&amp;lt;task_name&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e">## Shows help for the &amp;lt;task_name&amp;gt; task.&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene -h &amp;lt;task_name&amp;gt;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;em>--task=&amp;lt;task_name&amp;gt; [&amp;lt;task_parameter&amp;gt;=value &amp;hellip;]&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Specifies the task to run. A user-defined UGENE workflow schema can be used as a task name. For example:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene --task&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>align --in&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>COI.aln --out&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>result.aln
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ugene --task&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>C:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">\m&lt;/span>yschema.uwl --in&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>COI.aln --out&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>res.aln
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;em>--log-no-task-progress&lt;/em>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Creating Custom CLI Tasks</title><link>https://ugene.net/docs/ugene-command-line-interface/creating-custom-cli-tasks/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ugene.net/docs/ugene-command-line-interface/creating-custom-cli-tasks/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="creating-custom-cli-tasks">Creating Custom CLI Tasks&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>The &lt;a href="cli-predefined-tasks.md">&lt;em>predefined tasks&lt;/em>&lt;/a> are actually the &lt;a href="workflow-designer.md">&lt;em>Workflow Designer&lt;/em>&lt;/a> schemas stored in the $UGENE/data/cmdline directory.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Follow the instructions in the &lt;a href="https://ugene.unipro.ru/wiki/display/WDD/Workflow+Designer+Manual">Workflow Designer Manual&lt;/a> on how to create a schema and run it from the command line.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You may also find the following video tutorial useful, which is devoted to creating a custom console command:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZfxmX_2Ot5M">Creating custom console command (MUSCLE alignment with various output format)&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul></description></item></channel></rss>